post_text:
Meet the Executive Director of SCMSA!!

Hello, I am Tammy Bengtson, I am so excited for our students and staff to be together next week. This is my 7th year as the Executive Director at St. Cloud Math and Science Academy. I taught special education in Saint Cloud for twenty years before being hired in 2014 to open the St. Cloud Math and Science Academy Charter school. I love working at SCMSA because we are a small school with a positive climate. Our staff work together towards common goals and have some fun along the way. When I am not at work, I enjoy spending time with family and friends at our cabin up north. I enjoy boating, kayaking, four wheeling, playing cards, planting flowers, vacationing, karaoke and Zumba. My husband and I enjoy visiting our parents and spending time with our three adult children and our two sweet grandsons who call me Nana!

post_text:
Meet one of SCMSA's ELL teachers!

Hello, my name is Ms. Keniston. This will be my 2nd year at SCMSA and my 6th year of teaching. I have taught in Faribault, Saint Cloud, and Sauk Rapids. I was born, raised, and have lived in Minnesota for my whole life. I love to travel, watch movies, do jigsaw puzzles, play board games and card games, and cross-stitching.
I have three brothers, two sisters-in-law, and three nephews and two nieces. My mom and dad both have large families, so I also have many aunts, uncles, and cousins.
My favorite things are getting together with my family, watching new movies, and working on my cross stitch projects.
I joined SCMSA because I like that Mrs. Bengston creates a kind, safe, and accepting environment for the staff and students. I love teaching English as a part of different content areas, especially science and social studies, so I am wonderfully happy at SCMSA.

post_text:
Meet our Speech Language Pathologist

Greetings! My name is Mrs. Johnson and I am the speech-language pathologist (SLP) here at SCMSA. I provide speech-language therapy to students who have communication needs. I am starting my 23rd school year as an SLP, this being my 4th year at SCMSA. I can be described as a “word nerd” who loves a great debate and kind people. When I may do whatever I choose, I enjoy spending time with my husband, our two daughters, and our 11 year old dog, staying active, spending time with friends and extended family, listening to 80s music & talk radio, watching the latest movies, binge watching a good Netflix or Amazon series, reading, and traveling to destinations near & far.

post_text:
Meet our Special Education Director!
Hello! I am Jill Waldvogel and welcome back to a new school year SCMSA Northerns! I’ve been working at St. Cloud Math and Science Academy-SCMSA since August 2014 as a special education teacher, coordinator, Title I math teacher, reading teacher, and currently as the assessment and special education director. I started in education in 1999 as a paraprofessional at North Junior High in St. Cloud. Since then, I have worked in schools all over St. Cloud, Royalton, and Willmar as a special education data and instructional coach. My passion is seeing student growth in reading-- it is so fun! I love spending time with my family, camping, boating, swimming, vacationing, and kayaking. I also love visiting my parents in Arizona with my family.

post_text:
Hello, my name is Mrs. Bodette: Reading Interventionist. My job is to teach students how to read and write. Teacher: 46 years. Grades K-8. High School Paraprofessional and Special Ed. teacher.

Started a school in my art studio: Designing Tomorrow.(1981-2020.) Bridging students to the next grade during the summer. Teaching art, reading, math, and writing.

As a reading interventionist it’s like being an educational detective. My job is to find a path to help students struggling in the area of reading and writing succeed.

St. Cloud Math and Science Academy is an outstanding school with a respectful and smart teaching environment.
MY MISSION: TEACH!

post_text:
One of our 2nd Grade Teachers

Hi, I’m Mrs. Hodge. I’ve been a teacher for 26 years, starting out my career in Cokato, Minnesota. After teaching twelve years at Cokato Elementary and getting my master degree in education, I moved around a bit with my husband Milton. I then taught in Kentucky, U.S. Virgin Islands, Colorado, and now the last three years at Saint Cloud Math and Science Academy.
It’s been wonderful to be back in Minnesota by my family of four grown children (and their spouses) and five grandchildren. We love to get together for simple things like dinners, camping, shopping, coffee, etc. When I’m by myself I like to quilt, read, surf on my phone/computer, decorate, paint, knit, play with my puppy Evie, watch baking shows, the news and all sorts of different series on TV, embroider dish towels, mix essential oil recipes, camping... Ha, ha! The list goes on...
I’ve taught every grade from 1st-5th. I’m part of the Leadership Team and teach Second Grade here at SCMSA. It’s a special, family centered place with the very best students and staff!

post_text:
Meet our Dean of Students

Hello! My name is Ms. Yiran, Dean of Students, and EL teacher at SCMSA since its founding. I started my teaching career in Cameroon, West Africa. I enjoy teaching English Language Learners who teach me about their cultures as much as they learn from them. Teaching at SCMSA continues to be an enriching and enjoyable experience enhanced by the outstanding team-work, and excited students, always eager to learn new things. When I am not teaching, I enjoy listening to music, walking, crocheting, reading, hanging out with my children, and organizing African Arts & Culture community events in the summer.

post_text: Today is National Teacher Appreciation Day. I would like to say thank you to the exceptional teachers at our school who play a critical role in educating our students and reaching our school goals. Our teachers are kind, patient, hard-working, dedicated and understanding. Since distance learning started, they have had daily interaction with their students and problem solved technology and grouping challenges to give their students the best education possible. I wish we could celebrate in person. I appreciate everyone of you today and always. Happy Teacher Appreciation week!

See you on Friday!

An Ostrich egg is the largest of all eggs. One ostrich egg is equal to 24 hen eggs. One ostrich egg has 2,000 calories, a chicken egg has about 72 (raw).

post_text:
Why do we have a STEM DAY at St. Cloud Math and Science Academy?
STEM is important because it is in every part of our lives. Science is everywhere in the world around us. ... By exposing students to STEM and giving them opportunities to explore STEM-related concepts, they will develop a passion for it and hopefully pursue a job in a STEM field!
text:
Why do we have a STEM DAY at St. Cloud Math and Science Academy?
STEM is important because it is in every part of our lives. Science is everywhere in the world around us. ... By exposing students to STEM and giving them opportunities to explore STEM-related concepts, they will develop a passion for it and hopefully pursue a job in a STEM field!

post_text:
Today we had an amazing STEM day!
What is STEM?
STEM is an acronym for the fields of science, technology, engineering and math. Discussion of STEM-related programs has become a presidential priority because too few college students are pursuing degrees in these fields.

post_text:
Third Grade! STEM DAY!
Students exploring the world of sound energy and music using basic materials.
Captivating.
What is sound energy? Sound is a type of energy made by vibrations. When any object vibrates, it causes movement in the air particles. These particles bump into the particles close to them, which makes them vibrate too causing them to bump into more air particles. This movement, called sound waves, keeps going until they run out of energy.
